Figure 3
). Arms moderately long, forearm length (FAL 16.6) shorter than hand length (HAL 17.9); relative length of fingers I <IV <II <III (FL I 8.9, FLII 11.0, FLIII 14.7, FLIV 10.3), tips of fingers with discs except on finger I, discs moderately wide compared to finger width except on finger I (FDI 1.9, FWI 1.8; FDII 2.3, FWII 1.1; FDIII 3.0, FWIII 1.1; FDIV 3.0, FWIV 1.1), finger discs with circummarginal grooves, except on finger I; dermal fringe present on fingers; webbing absent between fingers; subarticular tubercles rather prominent and rounded, formula 1, 1, 2, 2 (
